{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01Rpb5oUkJfBtCBCLYkUpPHb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The magnitudes are decisive: equilibrium xenon worth at 9 MW is ~1.6–2.1 k pcm (~2–3 dollars), and the post-trip xenon *peak* adds another ~400–1300 pcm beyond equilibrium (nominal ~1270 pcm at ~8 h). With α ≈ −7 pcm/K, compensating that requires ~180 K of extra overcooling — which takes hours. This is exactly the delaying mechanism. Now let me build the full coupled model."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1706,"cache_read_input_tokens":58549,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1706},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d6d8b148-c850-46f2-9bbc-b7461be96ce5","uuid":"b87f878f-683c-4b0a-a335-c334f74c380a","request_id":"req_011CcfX1frSjhhNqbdrGMNWC"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01Rpb5oUkJfBtCBCLYkUpPHb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HqcoYUHdEH4WG1VK6BPuXR","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/root/bench/httr_xenon/transient_xe.py","content":"\"\"\"\nHTTR LOFC coupled transient WITH Xe-135 / I-135 poisoning dynamics.\n\nThis extends transient.py (point kinetics + decay heat + 3-node graphite/vessel\nthermal model + VCS sink) by adding the iodine/xenon fission-product chain and\nfeeding the xenon reactivity worth into the same point-kinetics reactivity.\n\nReactivity channels now:\n  rho_total(t) = Drho_core(Tc)              # temperature feedback, from OpenMC k_inf(T)\n               + Drho_xe(t)                 # xenon CHANGE from pre-trip equilibrium\n\nAt t=0 the reactor is critical at 9 MWt with EQUILIBRIUM xenon already present\n(frozen rods hold criticality at T_op WITH that xenon). So the reactivity we track\nis the change from equilibrium: both channels are 0 at t=0.\n\nXenon bookkeeping (scaled to reactivity units to avoid needing an absolute Sigma_f):\n  Define  Xt = sigma_aX * N_Xe / (nu * Sigma_f)   (dimensionless; = -rho_Xe)\n          It = sigma_aX * N_I  / (nu * Sigma_f)\n  Flux ~ fission power, phi(t) = phi_9MW * P/P0, so the xenon burn rate is\n          omega(t) = omega_full * P/P0 ,  omega_full = sigma_aX * phi_9MW  [1/s]\n  dIt/dt = omega*gI/nu            - lamI*It\n  dXt/dt = omega*gX/nu + lamI*It  - lamX*Xt - omega*Xt\n  Drho_xe(t) = -(Xt(t) - Xt_eq)\n\nThe ONLY new physics knob that matters is omega_full = sigma_aX * phi_9MW (the\nxenon burn rate at operating flux); everything else (yields, decay constants, nu)\nis standard nuclear data. omega_full sets both the equilibrium worth and the\npost-trip peak. It carries the flux-level + effective-cross-section uncertainty.\n\"\"\"\nimport numpy as np\nfrom scipy.integrate import solve_ivp\nfrom scipy.interpolate import interp1d\nimport transient as TR   # reuse cp_graphite, decay_frac, load_kT, make_drho, BETA data\n\n# --- Xe/I nuclear data (standard, U-235 thermal) -----------------------------\nLN2  = np.log(2.0)\nT_I  = 6.57*3600.0        # I-135 half-life [s]  (t1/2 ~ 6.6 h)\nT_X  = 9.14*3600.0        # Xe-135 half-life [s] (t1/2 ~ 9.1 h)\nLAM_I_XE = LN2/T_I        # 2.93e-5 /s\nLAM_X    = LN2/T_X        # 2.11e-5 /s\nGAMMA_I  = 0.0629         # I-135 cumulative fission yield (U-235 thermal)\nGAMMA_X  = 0.00237        # Xe-135 direct (independent) fission yield\nNU       = 2.43           # neutrons per thermal fission, U-235\n\ndef xe_equilibrium(omega_full):\n    \"\"\"Pre-trip equilibrium It, Xt at operating flux. Xt_eq = -rho_Xe_eq.\"\"\"\n    It_eq = omega_full*GAMMA_I/(NU*LAM_I_XE)\n    Xt_eq = omega_full*(GAMMA_I+GAMMA_X)/NU/(LAM_X + omega_full)\n    return It_eq, Xt_eq\n\ndef run_xe(params, drho_core, beta_eff, omega_full, verbose=False):\n    \"\"\"Coupled transient with xenon. params/drho_core/beta_eff as in transient.run.\"\"\"\n    p = params\n    Top = p['Top']; P0 = p['P0']\n    Mc = p['Mc']; Mr = p['Mr']; Mv = p.get('Mv',100000.0)\n    Gcr = p['Gcr']; Grv = p.get('Grv',4000.0)\n    Q0 = p['Q0']; Ts = p['Ts']; pexp = p['pexp']\n    t_op = p['t_op']; Lam = p['Lam']; L0 = p.get('L0',0.6e6)\n    cp_v = 500.0\n\n    Tr_op = Top - L0/Gcr\n    Tv_op = Tr_op - L0/Grv\n\n    beta_i = TR.BETA_I*(beta_eff/TR.BETA0)\n    b_eff  = beta_i.sum()\n    S = p.get('S',1e-6)*P0\n\n    It_eq, Xt_eq = xe_equilibrium(omega_full)\n\n    def Qvcs(Tv):\n        return Q0*np.maximum((Tv-Ts)/(Tv_op-Ts),0.0)**pexp\n\n    C0 = beta_i/(TR.LAM_I*Lam)*P0\n    y0 = np.concatenate([[P0], C0, [Top,Tr_op,Tv_op], [It_eq, Xt_eq]])\n\n    def rhs(t,y):\n        P  = max(y[0],0.0)\n        C  = np.maximum(y[1:7],0.0)\n        Tc,Tr,Tv = y[7],y[8],y[9]\n        It = max(y[10],0.0); Xt = max(y[11],0.0)\n        # reactivity: temperature feedback + xenon change from equilibrium\n        rho = drho_core(Tc) - (Xt - Xt_eq)\n        dP  = (rho - b_eff)/Lam*P + np.dot(TR.LAM_I,C) + S\n        dC  = beta_i/Lam*P - TR.LAM_I*C\n        Pd  = TR.decay_frac(t,t_op)*P0\n        qcr = Gcr*(Tc-Tr); qrv = Grv*(Tr-Tv)\n        dTc = (P + Pd - qcr)/(Mc*TR.cp_graphite(Tc))\n        dTr = (qcr - qrv)/(Mr*TR.cp_graphite(Tr))\n        dTv = (qrv - Qvcs(Tv))/(Mv*cp_v)\n        # xenon chain; burn rate scales with fission power (flux ~ P)\n        omega = omega_full*(P/P0)\n        dIt = omega*GAMMA_I/NU              - LAM_I_XE*It\n        dXt = omega*GAMMA_X/NU + LAM_I_XE*It - LAM_X*Xt - omega*Xt\n        return np.concatenate([[dP],dC,[dTc,dTr,dTv],[dIt,dXt]])\n\n    t_end = p.get('t_end', 6.0*24*3600)\n    teval = np.unique(np.concatenate([np.linspace(0,600,200),\n                                      np.linspace(600,t_end,6000)]))\n    sol = solve_ivp(rhs,(0,t_end),y0,method='BDF',t_eval=teval,\n                    rtol=1e-6,atol=[1e-2]+[1e-2]*6+[1e-3,1e-3,1e-3]+[1e-9,1e-9],\n                    max_step=120.0)\n    return sol, b_eff, Xt_eq\n\ndef summarize_xe(sol, P0, Top, Xt_eq):\n    t=sol.t; P=sol.y[0]; Tc=sol.y[7]; Tr=sol.y[8]; Tv=sol.y[9]\n    It=sol.y[10]; Xt=sol.y[11]\n    i30=max(np.searchsorted(t,1800),3)\n    Pmin_early=P[:i30].min(); tmin=t[:i30][np.argmin(P[:i30])]\n    ipk=np.argmax(Tc); Tc_peak=Tc[ipk]; tpeak=t[ipk]\n    # recriticality: first time AFTER the initial collapse that fission power\n    # climbs back through a threshold (self-sustaining). Use P recovering to a\n    # small fraction of P0 as the operational marker, then refine to reactivity=0.\n    # Robust marker: first local minimum of Tc is the deepest overcool; but with\n    # xenon the return-to-critical is when rho_total crosses 0 from below.\n    # We detect the fission-power revival: P rising back above 1 kW after collapse.\n    trec=None\n    thr = 1.0e3   # 1 kW\n    collapsed=False\n    for i in range(1,len(t)):\n        if not collapsed and P[i] < 1.0e2:   # <100 W => collapsed\n            collapsed=True\n        if collapsed and P[i] >= thr:\n            # interpolate crossing of thr\n            t0,t1=t[i-1],t[i]; y0v,y1v=P[i-1]-thr,P[i]-thr\n            trec=t0+(t1-t0)*(y0v/(y0v-y1v)) if y1v!=y0v else t1\n            break\n    # xenon peak (max additional negative reactivity beyond equilibrium)\n    dxe = -(Xt - Xt_eq)          # reactivity change (pcm/1e5); negative during peak\n    ixp = np.argmin(dxe); dxe_peak = dxe[ixp]; txe_peak=t[ixp]\n    n=max(int(0.1*len(t)),5); P_stab=np.mean(P[-n:])\n    return dict(Pmin_early=Pmin_early,tmin=tmin,trec=trec,\n                Tc_peak=Tc_peak,tpeak=tpeak,P_stab=P_stab,\n                Tc_end=Tc[-1],Tr_end=Tr[-1],P_end=P[-1],\n                Tv_peak=Tv.max(),Tv_end=Tv[-1],\n                Tc_min_post=Tc[ipk:].min() if ipk<len(t)-1 else Tc[-1],\n                dxe_peak_pcm=dxe_peak*1e5, txe_peak=txe_peak,\n                Xt_eq_pcm=Xt_eq*1e5)\n\nif __name__=='__main__':\n    import sys\n    Tk,kk,sk = TR.load_kT('runs/main/keff.csv',bp=1)\n    Top=823.0\n    drho,kfun = TR.make_drho(Tk,kk,Top)\n    beta_eff=0.007276\n    sigma_aX=2.0e6*1e-24   # cm^2 (effective)\n    phi_9MW =3.0e13        # n/cm^2/s (avg thermal flux at 9 MW)\n    omega_full=sigma_aX*phi_9MW\n    It_eq,Xt_eq=xe_equilibrium(omega_full)\n    print(f\"omega_full={omega_full:.3e}/s  rho_Xe_eq={-Xt_eq*1e5:.0f} pcm\")\n    base=dict(Top=Top,P0=9e6,Mc=14000.0,Mr=45000.0,Mv=100000.0,\n              Gcr=2000.0,Grv=2500.0,Q0=0.3e6,L0=0.3e6,Ts=320.0,pexp=1.5,\n              t_op=30*24*3600.0,Lam=1e-3,t_end=6.0*24*3600,S=1e-6)\n    sol,beff,Xeq=run_xe(base,drho,beta_eff,omega_full)\n    s=summarize_xe(sol,base['P0'],Top,Xeq)\n    for k_,v in s.items(): print(f\"  {k_}: {v}\")\n    print(f\"  trec_h={s['trec']/3600 if s['trec'] else None}\")\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1706,"cache_read_input_tokens":58549,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1706},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d6d8b148-c850-46f2-9bbc-b7461be96ce5","uuid":"5856c6ce-9683-44b9-a5f8-9a581493b653","request_id":"req_011CcfX1frSjhhNqbdrGMNWC"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HqcoYUHdEH4WG1VK6BPuXR","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /root/bench/httr_xenon/transient_xe.py (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d6d8b148-c850-46f2-9bbc-b7461be96ce5","uuid":"fabb466b-456b-4559-9f9b-aafadd4e8ffd","timestamp":"2026-07-03T17:29:17.990Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/root/bench/httr_xenon/transient_xe.py","content":"\"\"\"\nHTTR LOFC coupled transient WITH Xe-135 / I-135 poisoning dynamics.\n\nThis extends transient.py (point kinetics + decay heat + 3-node graphite/vessel\nthermal model + VCS sink) by adding the iodine/xenon fission-product chain and\nfeeding the xenon reactivity worth into the same point-kinetics reactivity.\n\nReactivity channels now:\n  rho_total(t) = Drho_core(Tc)              # temperature feedback, from OpenMC k_inf(T)\n               + Drho_xe(t)                 # xenon CHANGE from pre-trip equilibrium\n\nAt t=0 the reactor is critical at 9 MWt with EQUILIBRIUM xenon already present\n(frozen rods hold criticality at T_op WITH that xenon). So the reactivity we track\nis the change from equilibrium: both channels are 0 at t=0.\n\nXenon bookkeeping (scaled to reactivity units to avoid needing an absolute Sigma_f):\n  Define  Xt = sigma_aX * N_Xe / (nu * Sigma_f)   (dimensionless; = -rho_Xe)\n          It = sigma_aX * N_I  / (nu * Sigma_f)\n  Flux ~ fission power, phi(t) = phi_9MW * P/P0, so the xenon burn rate is\n          omega(t) = omega_full * P/P0 ,  omega_full = sigma_aX * phi_9MW  [1/s]\n  dIt/dt = omega*gI/nu            - lamI*It\n  dXt/dt = omega*gX/nu + lamI*It  - lamX*Xt - omega*Xt\n  Drho_xe(t) = -(Xt(t) - Xt_eq)\n\nThe ONLY new physics knob that matters is omega_full = sigma_aX * phi_9MW (the\nxenon burn rate at operating flux); everything else (yields, decay constants, nu)\nis standard nuclear data. omega_full sets both the equilibrium worth and the\npost-trip peak. It carries the flux-level + effective-cross-section uncertainty.\n\"\"\"\nimport numpy as np\nfrom scipy.integrate import solve_ivp\nfrom scipy.interpolate import interp1d\nimport transient as TR   # reuse cp_graphite, decay_frac, load_kT, make_drho, BETA data\n\n# --- Xe/I nuclear data (standard, U-235 thermal) -----------------------------\nLN2  = np.log(2.0)\nT_I  = 6.57*3600.0        # I-135 half-life [s]  (t1/2 ~ 6.6 h)\nT_X  = 9.14*3600.0        # Xe-135 half-life [s] (t1/2 ~ 9.1 h)\nLAM_I_XE = LN2/T_I        # 2.93e-5 /s\nLAM_X    = LN2/T_X        # 2.11e-5 /s\nGAMMA_I  = 0.0629         # I-135 cumulative fission yield (U-235 thermal)\nGAMMA_X  = 0.00237        # Xe-135 direct (independent) fission yield\nNU       = 2.43           # neutrons per thermal fission, U-235\n\ndef xe_equilibrium(omega_full):\n    \"\"\"Pre-trip equilibrium It, Xt at operating flux. Xt_eq = -rho_Xe_eq.\"\"\"\n    It_eq = omega_full*GAMMA_I/(NU*LAM_I_XE)\n    Xt_eq = omega_full*(GAMMA_I+GAMMA_X)/NU/(LAM_X + omega_full)\n    return It_eq, Xt_eq\n\ndef run_xe(params, drho_core, beta_eff, omega_full, verbose=False):\n    \"\"\"Coupled transient with xenon. params/drho_core/beta_eff as in transient.run.\"\"\"\n    p = params\n    Top = p['Top']; P0 = p['P0']\n    Mc = p['Mc']; Mr = p['Mr']; Mv = p.get('Mv',100000.0)\n    Gcr = p['Gcr']; Grv = p.get('Grv',4000.0)\n    Q0 = p['Q0']; Ts = p['Ts']; pexp = p['pexp']\n    t_op = p['t_op']; Lam = p['Lam']; L0 = p.get('L0',0.6e6)\n    cp_v = 500.0\n\n    Tr_op = Top - L0/Gcr\n    Tv_op = Tr_op - L0/Grv\n\n    beta_i = TR.BETA_I*(beta_eff/TR.BETA0)\n    b_eff  = beta_i.sum()\n    S = p.get('S',1e-6)*P0\n\n    It_eq, Xt_eq = xe_equilibrium(omega_full)\n\n    def Qvcs(Tv):\n        return Q0*np.maximum((Tv-Ts)/(Tv_op-Ts),0.0)**pexp\n\n    C0 = beta_i/(TR.LAM_I*Lam)*P0\n    y0 = np.concatenate([[P0], C0, [Top,Tr_op,Tv_op], [It_eq, Xt_eq]])\n\n    def rhs(t,y):\n        P  = max(y[0],0.0)\n        C  = np.maximum(y[1:7],0.0)\n        Tc,Tr,Tv = y[7],y[8],y[9]\n        It = max(y[10],0.0); Xt = max(y[11],0.0)\n        # reactivity: temperature feedback + xenon change from equilibrium\n        rho = drho_core(Tc) - (Xt - Xt_eq)\n        dP  = (rho - b_eff)/Lam*P + np.dot(TR.LAM_I,C) + S\n        dC  = beta_i/Lam*P - TR.LAM_I*C\n        Pd  = TR.decay_frac(t,t_op)*P0\n        qcr = Gcr*(Tc-Tr); qrv = Grv*(Tr-Tv)\n        dTc = (P + Pd - qcr)/(Mc*TR.cp_graphite(Tc))\n        dTr = (qcr - qrv)/(Mr*TR.cp_graphite(Tr))\n        dTv = (qrv - Qvcs(Tv))/(Mv*cp_v)\n        # xenon chain; burn rate scales with fission power (flux ~ P)\n        omega = omega_full*(P/P0)\n        dIt = omega*GAMMA_I/NU              - LAM_I_XE*It\n        dXt = omega*GAMMA_X/NU + LAM_I_XE*It - LAM_X*Xt - omega*Xt\n        return np.concatenate([[dP],dC,[dTc,dTr,dTv],[dIt,dXt]])\n\n    t_end = p.get('t_end', 6.0*24*3600)\n    teval = np.unique(np.concatenate([np.linspace(0,600,200),\n                                      np.linspace(600,t_end,6000)]))\n    sol = solve_ivp(rhs,(0,t_end),y0,method='BDF',t_eval=teval,\n                    rtol=1e-6,atol=[1e-2]+[1e-2]*6+[1e-3,1e-3,1e-3]+[1e-9,1e-9],\n                    max_step=120.0)\n    return sol, b_eff, Xt_eq\n\ndef summarize_xe(sol, P0, Top, Xt_eq):\n    t=sol.t; P=sol.y[0]; Tc=sol.y[7]; Tr=sol.y[8]; Tv=sol.y[9]\n    It=sol.y[10]; Xt=sol.y[11]\n    i30=max(np.searchsorted(t,1800),3)\n    Pmin_early=P[:i30].min(); tmin=t[:i30][np.argmin(P[:i30])]\n    ipk=np.argmax(Tc); Tc_peak=Tc[ipk]; tpeak=t[ipk]\n    # recriticality: first time AFTER the initial collapse that fission power\n    # climbs back through a threshold (self-sustaining). Use P recovering to a\n    # small fraction of P0 as the operational marker, then refine to reactivity=0.\n    # Robust marker: first local minimum of Tc is the deepest overcool; but with\n    # xenon the return-to-critical is when rho_total crosses 0 from below.\n    # We detect the fission-power revival: P rising back above 1 kW after collapse.\n    trec=None\n    thr = 1.0e3   # 1 kW\n    collapsed=False\n    for i in range(1,len(t)):\n        if not collapsed and P[i] < 1.0e2:   # <100 W => collapsed\n            collapsed=True\n        if collapsed and P[i] >= thr:\n            # interpolate crossing of thr\n            t0,t1=t[i-1],t[i]; y0v,y1v=P[i-1]-thr,P[i]-thr\n            trec=t0+(t1-t0)*(y0v/(y0v-y1v)) if y1v!=y0v else t1\n            break\n    # xenon peak (max additional negative reactivity beyond equilibrium)\n    dxe = -(Xt - Xt_eq)          # reactivity change (pcm/1e5); negative during peak\n    ixp = np.argmin(dxe); dxe_peak = dxe[ixp]; txe_peak=t[ixp]\n    n=max(int(0.1*len(t)),5); P_stab=np.mean(P[-n:])\n    return dict(Pmin_early=Pmin_early,tmin=tmin,trec=trec,\n                Tc_peak=Tc_peak,tpeak=tpeak,P_stab=P_stab,\n                Tc_end=Tc[-1],Tr_end=Tr[-1],P_end=P[-1],\n                Tv_peak=Tv.max(),Tv_end=Tv[-1],\n                Tc_min_post=Tc[ipk:].min() if ipk<len(t)-1 else Tc[-1],\n                dxe_peak_pcm=dxe_peak*1e5, txe_peak=txe_peak,\n                Xt_eq_pcm=Xt_eq*1e5)\n\nif __name__=='__main__':\n    import sys\n    Tk,kk,sk = TR.load_kT('runs/main/keff.csv',bp=1)\n    Top=823.0\n    drho,kfun = TR.make_drho(Tk,kk,Top)\n    beta_eff=0.007276\n    sigma_aX=2.0e6*1e-24   # cm^2 (effective)\n    phi_9MW =3.0e13        # n/cm^2/s (avg thermal flux at 9 MW)\n    omega_full=sigma_aX*phi_9MW\n    It_eq,Xt_eq=xe_equilibrium(omega_full)\n    print(f\"omega_full={omega_full:.3e}/s  rho_Xe_eq={-Xt_eq*1e5:.0f} pcm\")\n    base=dict(Top=Top,P0=9e6,Mc=14000.0,Mr=45000.0,Mv=100000.0,\n              Gcr=2000.0,Grv=2500.0,Q0=0.3e6,L0=0.3e6,Ts=320.0,pexp=1.5,\n              t_op=30*24*3600.0,Lam=1e-3,t_end=6.0*24*3600,S=1e-6)\n    sol,beff,Xeq=run_xe(base,drho,beta_eff,omega_full)\n    s=summarize_xe(sol,base['P0'],Top,Xeq)\n    for k_,v in s.items(): print(f\"  {k_}: {v}\")\n    print(f\"  trec_h={s['trec']/3600 if s['trec'] else None}\")\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
